# Implementation Plan - Department and Position CRUDs

Implement CRUD functionality for [Department](file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Domain/Entities/Department.cs#5-11) and [Position](file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Domain/Entities/Position.cs#5-14) entities following Clean Architecture, using a generic service base and specific repositories.

## Proposed Changes

### [Domain Layer]
- #### [NEW] IDepartmentRepository.cs (file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Domain/Interfaces/IDepartmentRepository.cs)
  Interface for Department repository inheriting from `IGenericRepository<Department>`.
- #### [NEW] IPositionRepository.cs (file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Domain/Interfaces/IPositionRepository.cs)
  Interface for Position repository inheriting from `IGenericRepository<Position>`.

### [Infrastructure Layer]
- #### [NEW] DepartmentRepository.cs (file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Infrastructure.Persistence/Repositories/DepartmentRepository.cs)
  Implementation using `GenericRepository<Department>` and [ApplicationDbContext](file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Infrastructure.Persistence/Contexts/ApplicationDbContext.cs#7-28).
- #### [NEW] PositionRepository.cs (file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Infrastructure.Persistence/Repositories/PositionRepository.cs)
  Implementation using `GenericRepository<Position>` and [ApplicationDbContext](file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Infrastructure.Persistence/Contexts/ApplicationDbContext.cs#7-28).
- #### [MODIFY] ServiceRegistration.cs (file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Infrastructure.Persistence/ServiceRegistration.cs)
  Register `IDepartmentRepository` and `IPositionRepository`.

### [Application Layer]
- #### [NEW] DTOs
  - `DepartmentDto`, `DepartmentInsertDto`, `DepartmentUpdateDto` (file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Application/Dtos/Department/)
  - `PositionDto`, `PositionInsertDto`, `PositionUpdateDto` (file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Application/Dtos/Position/)
- #### [NEW] Service Interfaces
  - `IDepartmentService.cs` (file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Application/Interfaces/Department/IDepartmentService.cs)
  - `IPositionService.cs` (file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Application/Interfaces/Position/IPositionService.cs)
- #### [NEW] Service Implementations
  - `DepartmentService.cs` (file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Application/Services/Department/DepartmentService.cs): Overrides [InsertPreProcessing](file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Application/Services/Common/ServiceBase.cs#47-52) and [UpdatePreProcessing](file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Application/Services/Common/ServiceBase.cs#97-102) to ensure unique names.
  - `PositionService.cs` (file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Application/Services/Position/PositionService.cs): Overrides [InsertPreProcessing](file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Application/Services/Common/ServiceBase.cs#47-52) and [UpdatePreProcessing](file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Application/Services/Common/ServiceBase.cs#97-102) to validate `DepartmentId` existence.
- #### [NEW] AutoMapper Profiles
  - `DepartmentProfile.cs` (file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Application/Mappings/Department/DepartmentProfile.cs)
  - `PositionProfile.cs` (file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Application/Mappings/Position/PositionProfile.cs)
- #### [MODIFY] ServiceRegistration.cs (file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Core.Application/ServiceRegistration.cs)
  Register new services.

### [Presentation Layer (Optional but recommended for CRUD)]
- #### [NEW] DepartmentsController.cs (file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Presentation.Api/Controllers/DepartmentsController.cs)
- #### [NEW] PositionsController.cs (file:///c:/Users/pluto/source/repos/SiruBackend/SIRU.Presentation.Api/Controllers/PositionsController.cs)

## Business Rules implementation
1. **Department Unique Name**: In `DepartmentService.InsertPreProcessing`, use `_repository.FindAsync` to check if another department with the same name exists (case-insensitive if possible/needed).
2. **Position Department Validation**: In `PositionService.InsertPreProcessing`, check if `DepartmentId` exists using `_departmentRepository`.
3. **Non-null names**: Use `[Required]` and `[MinLength(1)]` attributes in DTOs.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Create unit tests for `DepartmentService` and `PositionService` in `SIRU.Tests.UnitTests`.
- Run tests using: `dotnet test SIRU.Tests.UnitTests`

### Manual Verification
- Use Swagger UI (`/swagger`) to:
  - Create a Department.
  - Try to create another Department with the same name (should fail).
  - Create a Position with a valid `DepartmentId`.
  - Try to create a Position with an invalid `DepartmentId` (should fail).
  - List, update, and delete.
